openaiSpec.name: generate_image_with_google_imagen

prompt.description: A detailed description of the image to be generated. Be specific about the subject, style, composition, lighting, colors, and any other relevant details.

negativePrompt.description: Describe elements or concepts that should *not* be included in the generated image. This helps to refine the output and avoid unwanted results.

openaiSpec.description: Generates images using Google's Imagen model.  Provide a detailed prompt and, optionally, a negative prompt to guide the generation.

userSettings.name: PROJECT_ID
userSettings.label: Google Cloud Project ID
userSettings.description: Your Google Cloud project ID. Can be found in the Google Cloud Console (https://console.cloud.google.com/).

userSettings.name: REGION
userSettings.label: Google Cloud Region
userSettings.description: The Google Cloud region to use (e.g., us-central1). Available regions can be found at https://cloud.google.com/vertex-ai/docs/general/locations.

userSettings.name: model
userSettings.label: Imagen Model
userSettings.description: Select the Imagen model to use. -002 is the newest, -001 is an earlier version, and -fast-001 is optimized for speed. Default: imagen-4.0-fast-generate-001.

userSettings.name: sampleCount
userSettings.label: Number of Images
userSettings.description: The number of images to generate (1-8). Default: 1.

userSettings.name: aspectRatio
userSettings.label: Aspect Ratio
userSettings.description: The aspect ratio of the generated image. Default: 1:1.

userSettings.name: imageQuality
userSettings.label: Image Quality
userSettings.description: The image quality. Choose enhanced for better quality. Default: standard.

userSettings.name: personGeneration
userSettings.label: Person Generation
userSettings.description: Controls whether the generated images can include people. `dont_allow`: No people. `allow_adult`: Adults only. `allow_all`: All ages. Default: allow_adult.

userSettings.name: safetySetting
userSettings.label: Safety Setting
userSettings.description: Controls the safety filters. `block_low_and_above`: Strongest filtering. `block_medium_and_above`: Balanced filtering (Default). `block_only_high`: Fewer filters. `block_none`: Minimal filtering (restricted access).
